channel.title: First computer i've built
channel.description:
yay another build thread. but anyways this is my first ever build. it took me around 10 hours total cause i read each book thoroughly to make sure i understood it. it was awesome, but i got a major ass headache. anyways, heres the shhpecs.
-RAIDMAX SMILODON Foldout Case http://www.newegg.com/Product/Product.aspx?Item=N82E16811156063 *the case is badass because the side are like car doors and they open up, instead of reaching inside.
-AMD Phenom II X2 555 Callisto 3.2GHz http://www.newegg.com/Product/Product.aspx?Item=N82E16819103846
-Kingston HyperX 3GB (3 x 1GB) 240-Pin DDR3 SDRAM DDR3 1600 http://www.newegg.com/Product/Product.aspx?Item=N82E16820104115&cm_re=kingston_hyperx_ddr3_1gb-_-20-104-115-_-Product
-ZOTAC GeForce 9500 GT 1GB 128-bit GDDR2 PCI Express 2.0 x16 http://www.newegg.com/Product/Product.aspx?Item=N82E16814500147
-350gb(i think) seagate SATA + external 500gb western digital hdd *couldn't find link
-ASUS M4A79XTD EVO AM3 AMD 790X ATX AMD Motherboard http://www.newegg.com/Product/Product.aspx?Item=N82E16813131402
-Windows 7 Ultimate x64
but thats about it. what do you think? i also have a dvd drive. But it was around 600 U.S. dollars. I also wanted a quad core, but didn't have enough $$. I'm also wondering thoughts on DDR3 vs. DDR2. :confused:
i have a pic of me working on the motherboard but cant post due to shitty school internet. will post later if anyone cares.

really? thats awesome. i read that some manufactuers overclock some processors and underclock some. so you go into buy a dual core and come out with a quad instead. pretty kickass imo.

and yes i need a new graphics card now lol. i bought Bad Company 2, and cant play it on high which pisses me off.
